# NEP89 fine-tuning template
# Fine-tune the NEP89 foundation model for a specific material.
# Requires BOTH nep89_20250409.txt AND nep89_20250409.restart.
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - Descriptor parameters (cutoff, n_max, basis_size, l_max, neuron, zbl)
#   MUST match the base model — they cannot be changed.
# - Only training-control parameters can vary (lambda_*, batch, generation).
# - The type line lists ONLY the species in your new dataset, but in an
#   order compatible with the base model's convention.

fine_tune  nep89_20250409.txt nep89_20250409.restart
type       2  Mo  S
# Descriptor — locked to base model
version    4
zbl        2
cutoff     6 5
n_max      4 4
basis_size 8 8
l_max      4 2 1
neuron     80

# Training control — adjustable
lambda_1   0
lambda_e   1.0
lambda_f   1.0
lambda_v   0.1
batch      1000
population 50
generation 5000    # fine-tuning converges faster; increase to 10000-50000 for large domain shifts
